cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.NE, cs.RO

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with analyzing videos of patients to estimate their 3D body pose and classify gait-related health problems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the proposed system uses Deep Neural Networks for classification. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another possible category as the system is designed for practical use in home environments for consistent gait monitoring. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses Deep Neural Networks for classification. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also a possible category as the system involves analyzing human movement and could have applications in robotics for human-robot interaction.
